parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission hesitation and hard shifting can cause accidents or near-misses, especially in situations where quick acceleration is necessary to avoid collisions.
symptoms: Transmission hesitates and shifts very hard into the next gear
transmission acts up and then returns to normal after shutting off and restarting the car

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission fluid leaks and failure can cause damage to the transmission and other components, leading to costly repairs and potentially causing accidents.

symptoms: Vehicle rolls away while parked on an incline

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration and transmission issues can cause loss of control, accidents, and potentially lead to injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle lurches forward or backward when shifting into gear
and may experience sudden and unexpected movements.

keyless start button makes a clicking sound
